text: Llawi Imaña (Aymara llawi padlock, imaña to guard, to hide, to bury, see: Candado and Imaña also spelled Llavi Imana) is a mountain in the Andes of Bolivia. It is situated in the La Paz Department, Larecaja Province, Sorata Municipality, north of the Cordillera Real. == See also == * Wila Wilani == References == Category:Mountains of La Paz Department (Bolivia)
title: Llawi Imaña
